---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import HorizontalCard from "../components/HorizontalCard.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Services" sideBarActiveItemID="services">
  <div>
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold mb-5">Consulting &amp; Data Science Services</div>
    <div class="text-lg mb-8 text-base-content/70">
      If you have biological data that's too <b>large</b> or too <b>complex</b> to analyze with off-the-shelf tools - that's exactly the kind of problem I find interesting.
      I offer consulting and applied data science services for academic labs, biotech companies, and research organizations.
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-10">
    <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md border border-base-300">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title text-xl">Biomedical Image Analysis</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/70">
          Custom pipelines for 2D and 3D biological image data — including cell segmentation, 
          object detection, and quantitative morphological analysis. 
          Specializing in light-sheet microscopy, high-content screening, and whole-brain imaging datasets.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-3">
          <span class="badge badge-outline">3D Segmentation</span>
          <span class="badge badge-outline">Light-sheet</span>
          <span class="badge badge-outline">HCS</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md border border-base-300">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title text-xl">Deep Learning for Biology</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/70">
          Training, fine-tuning, and deploying deep learning models for biological applications —
          including cell detection (StarDist, Cellpose), classification, 
          and custom architectures tailored to your specific imaging modality and research questions.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-3">
          <span class="badge badge-outline">StarDist</span>
          <span class="badge badge-outline">Cellpose</span>
          <span class="badge badge-outline">PyTorch</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md border border-base-300">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title text-xl">Statistical Analysis &amp; Bayesian Methods</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/70">
          Bayesian uncertainty quantification, parameter inference, and statistical modeling 
          for complex scientific datasets. From experimental design to publication-ready analysis 
          and visualization.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-3">
          <span class="badge badge-outline">Bayesian UQ</span>
          <span class="badge badge-outline">Parameter inference</span>
          <span class="badge badge-outline">Statistical modeling</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card bg-base-100 shadow-md border border-base-300">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h2 class="card-title text-xl">HPC &amp; Pipeline Development</h2>
        <p class="text-base-content/70">
          Optimizing computational workflows for large-scale data processing on HPC clusters. 
          Parallelization strategies (MPI, OpenMP), pipeline architecture, 
          and performance engineering for scientific computing workloads.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-3">
          <span class="badge badge-outline">HPC</span>
          <span class="badge badge-outline">MPI / OpenMP</span>
          <span class="badge badge-outline">Pipeline design</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <div class="mt-8 mb-4">
    <div class="text-2xl w-full font-bold mb-5">How I Work</div>
    <div class="text-base-content/70 mb-6">
      I typically engage in one of the following formats, depending on the scope and needs of your project:
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-10">
    <div class="card bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h3 class="card-title text-lg">Advisory</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
          Short-term consultation on methodology, pipeline design, or analysis strategy. 
          Ideal for teams that need expert guidance but will execute themselves.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h3 class="card-title text-lg">Project-based</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
          End-to-end development of a custom analysis pipeline or tool, 
          from requirements to delivery and documentation. 
          Typical engagements run 1–4 months.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card bg-base-200/50 border border-base-300">
      <div class="card-body">
        <h3 class="card-title text-lg">Collaboration</h3>
        <p class="text-sm text-base-content/70">
          Embedded collaboration as a computational partner on a research project, 
          contributing to analysis, methods development, and co-authorship.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="divider"></div>

  <div class="mt-8 mb-10 text-center">
    <div class="text-lg mb-4 text-base-content/70">
      Interested in working together? I'd love to hear about your project.
    </div>
    <a class="btn btn-primary" href="mailto:athena.economides@uzh.ch">
      Get in touch →
    </a>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
